│ 1. Understanding the Issue: The assertion failure occurs because the VPlan cost model selected VF=vscale x 2 (scalable vectorization factor with minimum 2 elements) while the legacy cost model selected      │
│ VF=vscale x 4. The assertion expects them to agree unless the VPlan contains additional simplifications not accounted for in the legacy model. The function `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` returned   │
