│ to ensure they are marked as ignored.                                                                                                                                                                          │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ However, the immediate fix is to adjust the assertion to allow disagreement for scalable vectors, as the cost models may differ in their handling. Alternatively, we could modify                              │
│ `planContainsAdditionalSimplifications` to also consider that dead code elimination may happen in VPlan but not be reflected in `CM.ValuesToIgnore`.                                                           │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Let's examine the assertion line. We'll modify it to allow disagreement when either width is scalable, since scalable cost modeling is less precise.                                                           │
